    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "### Create Version 3\r\n\r\n**Do This**:\r\n- Choose the third mood you described in your Activity Guide for you GIF.\r\n- Create a sequence of sounds that go with that mood and put it underneath your second sequence\r\n  - **Your sounds must last at least 6 measures!**\r\n  - You can click the header of the timeline to \"skip ahead\" in your song to the third backing track.\r\n- Create a third trigger with a new sound effect to go with your new backing track. \r\n\r\nWhen you are finished, you should have three backing tracks that play sequentially underneath the `when run` block and three `trigger` blocks. Here is an example of what this could look like.\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/573b93648f84e994e2c52be69466e66a-image-1745528533261.png)",
